20131958), [[Aide-de-camp]] to King [[George VI]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Arthur Edward Flynn Fawcus|Lt.-Col. A.E.F. Fawcus]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] (1886\u20131936), Commander, 1/5th [[Staffordshire Rangers|North Staffordshire Regiment]], 1/5th [[Sherwood Foresters]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /><ref>War Honours Won By Old Boys, Bedford Modern School, Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref><ref>Obituary, ''Lieut.-Col. Fawcus, A Fine War Record'', ''[[The Times]]'', 11 August 1936, p.14</ref>\n* [[William Francis Jackson|Lt.-Col. W. F. Jackson]] [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC&Bar]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] (1886\u20131964), Signals Liaison Officer to the US Army HQ in the UK during [[World War II]]<ref name=\"autogenerated37\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=37 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* [[George Croxton Walker|Major George Croxton Walker]] [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] (1888\u20131936)<ref>Obituary in ''[[Times & Citizen|The Bedford Times]]'', ''Major G. C. Walker'', ''Death of a Distinguished Military Officer'', 31 July 1936</ref><ref name=\"autogenerated17\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=17 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n* [[Edward Crozier Creasy|Major Edward Crozier Creasy]] (1888\u20131936), senior liaison Officer during the [[Upper Silesia Plebiscite]] (1920-21)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''MAJOR E. C. CREASY'', November 26, 1936, p.11</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/lifestory/1012374|title=Life story: Edward Crozier Creasy &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Wynn Bagnall|Captain Wynn Bagnall]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131931), [[Canadian Field Artillery]], model for a statue by [[James Earle Fraser (sculptor)|James Fraser]] in [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]]<ref>''The Eagle'' Vol. XII no. 9 (December 2015),p. 338</ref>\n* [[Melville Rysdale Ten Broeke|Lt.-Col. Melville Ten Broeke]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1891\u20131963), commander of [[Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry|Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry Regiment]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=je2Jz_1c21sC&pg=PA719&lpg=PA719&dq=ten+broeke+vancouver+imperial#v=onepage&q=ten%20broeke%20vancouver%20imperial|title=Imperial Vancouver Island|accessdate=13 March 2015|isbn=9781450059633|last1=Bosher|first1=J. F.|date=April 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Leonard Arthur Hawes|Major-General L.A. Hawes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1892\u20131986), Commanded the transport to France of the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War II)|BEF]] during [[World War I]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[W.C.V. Galwey|Brigadier W.C.V. Galwey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1897\u20131977), senior officer who served in [[World War I]] and [[World War II]]<ref name=\"Burke's Irish Family Records\" >Hugh Montgomery-Massingberd, ''Burke's Irish Family Records'' London, U.K.: Burkes Peerage Ltd, 1976</ref>\n* [[Ernest Dynes|Brigadier Ernest Dynes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903\u20131968), [[Aide-de-camp]] to HM Queen [[Elizabeth II]] (1955\u201357)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Thomas Henry Scott Galletly|Brigadier Thomas Henry Scott Galletly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1905\u20131972), Commander of the 1st Brigade, [[Arab League]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n* [[Major-General Reginald Booth Stockdale]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1908\u20131979) Colonel Commandant, [[REME]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Peter Boughey|Lt.-Col. Edward Peter Fletcher Boughey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1911\u20131986), [[Special Operations Executive]]<ref>Bedford Modern School. A.B.C. List. Easter Term 1923</ref>\n* [[Keith Burch|Major-General Keith Burch]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1931\u20132013)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n\n===Navy===\n* [[Willoughby Baynes Huddleston|Commander Willoughby Huddleston]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] (1866\u20131953), [[Aide-de-camp|ADC]] to [[John Sinclair, 1st Baron Pentland|Lord Pentland]], [[Governor of Madras]] (1912\u201319)<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Captain W.B. Huddleston'', 5 May 1953, p.8</ref>\n* [[Thomas Oloff de Wet|Captain Thomas Oloff de Wet]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1869\u20131940), Principal Naval Transport Officer during the [[Occupation of Constantinople|evacuation of Constantinople]] in 1923<ref>A Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]]. Compiled and Edited by H.E. Vipan.  Published in [[Bedford]] by W.J. Robinson, 1900.  School Honours; p. ix</ref>\n* [[Alfred Ransom (Royal Navy officer)|Rear Admiral Alfred Ransom]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1871\u20131953), senior officer in the Royal Navy<ref>H.E. Vipan,''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p. 103</ref>\n* [[Sir Ernest Whiteside Huddleston]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Royal Indian Navy|RIN]] (1874\u20131959), [[Aide-de-camp]] to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref