ber of parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Frederick Reginald Phipps|Major F. R. Phipps]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|A.M. Inst. C.E.]] F.S.I. (1875\u20131927), Senior Engineering Inspector at the [[Department of Transport|Ministry of Transport]], 1924 to 1927<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Major F. R. Phipps'', 12 January 1927, p.17</ref>\n* [[Sir Ralph Endersby Harwood]] [[Order of the Bath|KCB]] [[Royal Victorian Order|KCVO]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1883\u20131951). Financial Secretary to three Kings (1935\u201337)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Davenport Fabian Cartwright Blunt]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (1888\u20131965), [[Undersecretary|Under-Secretary]] at [[HM Treasury]] (1946\u201348)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Reginald Berkeley]] (1890\u20131935), [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Sir Laurence George Gale]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1905\u20131969). Controller, Royal Ordnance Factories<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Hugh Chaplin]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (1905\u20131996), Principal Keeper of Printed Books at the [[British Museum]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/incoming/obituary-a-h-chaplin-5586653.html|title=obituary: A. H. Chaplin|date=4 January 1997|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n* [[John Percival Morton|Jack Morton]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1911\u20131985). Assistant Undersecretary of State at the [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|Ministry of Defence]] (1968\u201371)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr Jack Morton'', 13 June 1985, p.12</ref>\n* [[Philip Lionel Burton]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1914\u20131996), Head of the Civil Service Pay Research Unit between 1963 and 1971<ref>The Harpur Trust, 1552\u20131973, by Joyce Godber, 1973</ref