0131928)|publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University}}</ref>\n* [[H.G. Graves|Henry George Graves]] [[Royal School of Mines|ARSM]] (1864\u20131929), Controller of [[Patent|Patents and Designs]] in India between 1904 and 1919<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr H.G. Graves'', 7 November 1929, p.19</ref>\n* [[Ernest Wilton|Sir Ernest Colville Collins Wilton]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|KCMG]] (1870\u20131952), President of the Commission for the Government of the [[Saar (League of Nations)|Saar Basin]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Herbert George Billson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1871\u20131938), Chief Conservator of Indian Forests, 1922\u201326<ref>''Who was Who Vol. III, 1929\u20131940'' (London, 1967), p. 111</ref>\n* [[Sir William Pell Barton]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|KCIE]] (1871\u20131956). [[Resident (title)|Resident]] in [[Vadodara|Baroda]] (1919), [[Mysore]] (1920\u201325) and [[Hyderabad]] (1925\u201330)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Sir W. Barton'', 29 November 1956, p.15</ref>\n* [[William McKinnell]] (1873\u20131939), politician who served in the Legislative Assembly of [[Manitoba]], Canada (1920\u201336)<ref>''Pioneers and Prominent People of Manitoba'', Published by Canadian Publicity Co., 1925</ref>\n* [[Walter Nutt (businessman)|Hon. Walter Nutt]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1874\u20131940), a member of the [[Federated Malay States|Federal Malay States]] [[Legislative council]]<ref>Colonial Armies in Southeast Asia, edited by Karl Hack and Tobias Rettig.  First published by [[Routledge]], 2006</ref>\n* [[John Richard Donovan Glascott]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1877\u20131938), Chief Engineer of the [[Myanmar Railways|Burma Railways]], Member of the [[Legislative Council of Burma]]<ref>The Eagle, BMS Magazine, Vol.XXI No.6, July 1938</ref>\n* [[Sir Robert Daniel Richmond]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1878\u20131948), Chief Conservator, Indian Woods and Forests<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Sir Daniel Richmond'', May 5, 1948, p.7</ref>\n* [[Archie Rose]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[FRGS]] (1879\u20131961), diplomat, explorer and businessman in China<ref>H.E. Vipan, A Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]], (Bedford, no date), p.107</ref>\n* [[Sir Francis Moncrieff Kerr-Jarrett]] (1885\u20131968), [[Custos Rotulorum]] of St James's, [[Jamaica]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Stanley Wyatt Smith]] (1887\u20131958), [[Consul (representative)|Consul-General]] of [[Manila]] (1938\u201342) and [[Honolulu]] (1943\u201344)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. S. Wyatt-Smith'', 19 November 1958, p.13</ref>\n* [[Ronald Okeden Alexander|Major-General Ronald Okeden Alexander]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1888\u20131949), Inspector General, Central Canada (1942\u201346)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Charles George Hawes|Charles Hawes]] [[Companion of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131963). Chief Engineer to the Government of [[Sind]]<ref>''Who was Who'' Vol. VI (1961\u201370) (London, 1972), p. 505</ref>\n* [[Frederick Williamson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1891\u20131935), [[Consul (representative)|Consul-General]] of [[Kashgar]] (1927\u201330)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''The Times'', ''Mr Frederick Williamson'', 19 November 1935, p.19</ref>\n* [[Reginald Philip Abigail]] (1892\u20131969), [[District Commissioner (British Colonial)|District Commissioner]] of [[Rakhine State|Arakan]] during the [[Japanese conquest of Burma|fall of Burma]] in 1942<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=PKIWAQAAIAAJ&dq=reginald+abigail+burma+kellys&q=abigail+bedford+modern|title=Kelly's Handbook to the Titled, Landed and Official Classes|accessdate=14 June 2015|year=1969|last1=Kelly's}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=oCUbAQAAIAAJ&