istinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1875\u20131969), [[field hockey]] player who competed in the [[1908 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Arthur Turner (British Army officer)|Arthur Jervois Turner]] (1878\u20131952), [[Cricket]]er and [[rugby union]] player<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Thomas Hammond (athlete)|Thomas Edgar Hammond]] (1878\u20131945), [[Track and field|track and field athlete]] who competed in the [[1908 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Sir Robert Daniel Richmond]] (1878\u20131948) played cricket for [[Jamaica]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Andrew Thomas Ralston|Andrew Ralston]] (1880\u20131950), amateur footballer for [[Tottenham Hotspur FC|Spurs]], [[Watford FC|Watford]]. [[Football Association|FA]] administrator.<ref>''The Eagle'' Vol. 27, no. 5 (1950), p. 391</ref>\n* [[Walter Turner (cricketer)|Walter Martin Fitzherbert Turner]] (1881\u20131948), [[Cricketer]]<ref>A Register of the Old Boys of [[Bedford Modern School]], Compiled and edited by H. E. Vipan, BA BSc.  Published Bedford by W.J. Robinson, 1900</ref>\n* [[Edgar Mobbs|Lt.-Col. Edgar Mobbs]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1882\u20131917), [[Captain (sports)|Captained]] the [[England national rugby union team|England Rugby Team]] and [[Northampton Saints|Northampton]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Arthur Cantrell]] (1883\u20131954), [[Cricketer]]<ref name=\"autogenerated10\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=10 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>  \n* [[Sidney Abrahams|Sir Sidney Abrahams]] [[Queen's Counsel|KC]] (1885\u20131957), competed in the [[Long jump]] at the [[Great Britain at the 1912 Summer Olympics|1912 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[N. D. T. Oliver|Norman Oliver]] [[Order of Aviz|CavA]] (1886\u20131948), played cricket for [[Bedfordshire County Cricket Club|Bedfordshire]] and [[Brazil]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Henry William Evans|Dr H.W. Evans]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131927), athlete, rugby player and physician<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pcm/articles/PMC2524788/?page=1|title=Dr Henry William Evans, British Medical Journal, 5th November, 1927, p. 850, retrieved July 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Gilbert Bull]] (1890\u20131963), [[England national rugby union team|England]] [[Rugby union|Rugby]] International<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Frederick Charles William Newman]] (1896\u20131966), cricketer<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Dick Stafford]] (1893\u20131912), [[England national rugby union team|England]] [[Rugby union|Rugby]] International<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Basil Rogers]] (1896\u20131975), [[Cricketer]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Harold Day (sportsman)|Harold Lindsay Vernon Day]] (1898\u20131972), [[England national rugby union team|England]] [[Rugby union|Rugby]] International who also played [[first class cricket]] for [[Hampshire C.C.C.|Hampshire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Ernest Dynes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903\u20131968), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Maurice Pugh]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1903\u20131986), [[Cricketer]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/14/14378/14378.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|website=cricketarchive.com}}</ref>\n* [[George Godber|Sir George Edward Godber]] [[Order of the Bath|GCB]] (1908\u20132009), rowed for [[University of Oxford|Oxford]] in the [[The Boat Race|1928 and 1929 Boat Races]]<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[G.T. 'Beef' Dancer]] (1911\u20131991), [[Rugby union|rugby]] player who participated in the [[1938 British Lions tour to South Africa]]<ref>100 Years of the Blues- The Bedfordshire Times Centenary History of Bedford R.U.F.C. (