ckinson Oxland|Air Vice-Marshal Robert Dickinson Oxland]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1889\u20131959), Group Commander in [[Bomber Command]] (1943\u201344)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Edye Rolleston Manning|Air Commodore Edye Rolleston Manning]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1889\u20131957), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=A1AfAQAAMAAJ&q=DSO+bedford+modern&dq=DSO+bedford+modern|title=The Aeroplane|accessdate=14 November 2015|year=1935}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Air CDRE. E.J. Manning'', 29 April 1957, p.12</ref>\n* [[Charles Henry Elliott-Smith|Air Commodore Charles Henry Elliott-Smith]] [[Air Force Cross (United Kingdom)|AFC]] (1889\u20131994), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref name=\"autogenerated49\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=49 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* [[H.D. Harvey-Kelly|Major H.D. Harvey-Kelly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1891\u20131917), Squadron Commander, [[Royal Flying Corps]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /><ref>The Eagle Vol. XIII no. 2 (July 1916), p. 24</ref>\n* [[John E. L. Hunter|Captain John Ellis Langford Hunter]] [[Distinguished Service Cross (United Kingdom)|DSC]] [[Distinguished Flying Cross (United Kingdom)|DFC]] (1897\u20131971), [[World War I]] [[flying ace]]<ref>''War Honours Won By Old Boys'', Bedford Modern School.  Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref>\n* [[Robert Cecil Dawkins|Group Captain Robert Cecil Dawkins]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903-1985), Station Commander at [[Tengah Air Base|RAF Tengah]] and [[Hendon Aerodrome|RAF Hendon]]<ref>''The Eagle'', The Magazine of [[Bedford Modern School]], Christmas 1951, Vol. XXVIII No.4</ref>\n* [[I. J. Fitch|Air Commodore I. J. Fitch]] (1903\u20131944), Deputy Director of Intelligence at the [[Air Ministry]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" /><ref>>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', 5 September 1944</ref>\n* [[Ernest Leslie 'Johnny' Hyde|Wing Commander Ernest Leslie 'Johnny' Hyde]] [[Distinguished Flying Cross (United Kingdom)|DFC]] (1914\u20131942), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.ww2awards.com/person/46312|title=World War 2 Awards.com \u2013 HYDE, Ernest Leslie|work=ww2awards.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Roland Lee Knight|Squadron Leader Roland Anthony 'Tony' Lee Knight]] [[Distinguished Flying Cross (United Kingdom)|DFC]] (1917\u20131941), [[World War II]] [[flying ace]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roll-of-honour.com/Bedfordshire/BedfordModernSchoolWW2Memorial.html|title=Roll of Honour \u2013 Bedfordshire \u2013 Bedford Modern School \u2013 World War 2|work=roll-of-honour.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Army===\n* [[Francis John Fowler|Major-General Francis John Fowler]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1864\u20131939) Commander of the [[Derajat Brigade]] (1914\u201316)<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Charles Astley Fowler|Major-General Charles Astley Fowler]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the Star of India|CSI]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1865\u20131940), Brigade Commander at the [[Battle of Loos]], 1915<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Arthur Long (Brigadier-General)|Brigadier-General Sir Arthur Long]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1866\u20131941), Director of Transport and Supplies, Macedonia and The Black Sea<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Reginald Ruston|Colonel Reginald Ruston]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (1867\u20131963), commander of the [[Mounted infantry]] of the [[Devonshire Regiment|Devon Regiment]] (1891\u20131903)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Robert Townshend Anwyl-Passingham|Major R.T. Anwyl-Passingham]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]] (1867\u20131926), Commander of the [[72nd Punjabis]], [[High sheriff|High Sheriff]] of [[Merionethshire]]<ref>Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]]. Compiled by H.E. Vipan. Published in [[Bedford]] by W. Robinson, 1900. Chapter IV, School Honours, p. vii</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/London/issue/33030/page/1874|title=Page 1874 &#124; Issue 33030, 17 March 1925 &#124; London Gazette &#124; The Gazette}}</ref>\n* [[Gerald Robert Poole|Lieutenant-General Gerald Robert Poole]] [[Companion of The Most Honourable Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Companion of the Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1868\u20131937), Commandant of the [[Royal Marine Artillery]]<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Charles Forbes Buchan|Lt.-Col. Charles Forbes Buchan]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Order of Saint John (chartered 1888)|OStJ]] (1869-1954), Deputy Assistant Director at the [[War Office]] during [[World War I|WW1]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', 3 May 1954, p.8</ref><ref>Obituary in The Eagle, The Magazine of Bedford Modern School, Summer 1954, Vol. XXIX No.6, p.483</ref>\n* [[Ernest Clive Atkins|Colonel Ernest Clive Atkins]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]] (1870\u20131953), Commander of the 2/5th [[Royal Leicestershire Regiment|Leicestershire Regiment]], [[High Sheriff of Leicestershire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/><ref>ATKINS OF HINCKLEY: 1722\u20131972 by J.S. Atkins. Atkins, Ltd. [[Hinckley]], 1972.  Page 40</ref>\n* [[Robert Leycester Haymes|Lt.-Col. Robert Haymes]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1870\u20131942), first to establish an [[Observation post|OP]] at the [[Battle of Neuve Chape