19&lpg=PA719&dq=ten+broeke+vancouver+imperial#v=onepage&q=ten%20broeke%20vancouver%20imperial|title=Imperial Vancouver Island|accessdate=13 March 2015|isbn=9781450059633|last1=Bosher|first1=J. F.|date=April 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Leonard Arthur Hawes|Major-General L.A. Hawes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1892\u20131986), Commanded the transport to France of the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War II)|BEF]] during [[World War I]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[W.C.V. Galwey|Brigadier W.C.V. Galwey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1897\u20131977), senior officer who served in [[World War I]] and [[World War II]]<ref name=\"Burke's Irish Family Records\" >Hugh Montgomery-Massingberd, ''Burke's Irish Family Records'' London, U.K.: Burkes Peerage Ltd, 1976</ref>\n* [[Ernest Dynes|Brigadier Ernest Dynes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903\u20131968), [[Aide-de-camp]] to HM Queen [[Elizabeth II]] (1955\u201357)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Thomas Henry Scott Galletly|Brigadier Thomas Henry Scott Galletly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1905\u20131972), Commander of the 1st Brigade, [[Arab League]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n* [[Major-General Reginald Booth Stockdale]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1908\u20131979) Colonel Commandant, [[REME]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Peter Boughey|Lt.-Col. Edward Peter Fletcher Boughey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1911\u20131986), [[Special Operations Executive]]<ref>Bedford Modern School. A.B.C. List. Easter Term 1923</ref>\n* [[Keith Burch|Major-General Keith Burch]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1931\u20132013)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n\n===Navy===\n* [[Willoughby Baynes Huddleston|Commander Willoughby Huddleston]] [[Order of St Michael